reviews.review_text: Great Show This is a great show, but unfortunately it will always be overshadowed by the other night at the Jai-alai fronton (the Dark Star-->Spanish Jam-->US Blues night). Only extended jams this night were on Playin' and Eyes, but the song selection was very good.

styles upon styles At about the 14:00 mark during "Playing in the Band" it suddenly sounds like Miles Davis' early 70's funk period.  A few minutes later it sounds like Pink Floyd circa "Ummagumma."

"bound to cover just a little more ground" indeed.

Very strong show.
